Davie decides to factor the number 756 into primes. After doing so, he makes a list from this factorization, including each prime in the list as many times as it appears in the factorization. What is the mode of his list?

}

\textbf{Answer:} The prime factorization of $756$ is $2^{2}\cdot3^{3}\cdot7$.  The list made from this factorization would be $2,2,3,3,3,7$.  The mode of the list is $\boxed{3}$.
